Date: 0/0/1882
Source: Brighter Britain
Author:
Vol / Page: 1/272
Edition:
Quote: English people are given to associating the idea of a `spree' with that of a bacchanal orgy. Not so We. With us the word is simply colonial for a festivity of any kind, public or private. And whatever may be the primary object of a spree, it is pretty certain to end with a dance.
Notes:

